Toddler-friendly TripAdvisor Recommendations¶

This project is inspired by lack of toddler-friendly travel attractions. Most recommendation engines use a broad age range when defining "kid-friendly" although what is appropriate for a 10-year-old may not be suitable or safe for a 3-year-old.

The preliminary analysis looks at two of the attractions in Maui, HI to see if there is indeed a gap between what is recommended and what is appropriate for a toddler (preliminary analysis of need).

The first attraction is Haleakala National Park. When filtered for things to do in Maui with kids, it is ranked second by travelers reviews. The reviews were limited to those containing the word "kid."

The second attraction is Baby Beach, which does not appear as one of the more popular destinations in Maui.

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
from wordcloud import WordCloud
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
In [2]:
# get partial reviews for Haleakala National Park
reviews = []
for n in range(0, 40, 10):
    if n == 0:
        r = requests.get('https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g60633-d2077822-Reviews-Haleakala_National_Park-Kula_Maui_Hawaii.html')
    else:
        r = requests.get('https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g60633-d2077822-Reviews-or{}-Haleakala_National_Park-Kula_Maui_Hawaii.html'.format(n))
    soup = BeautifulSoup(r.content, 'html.parser')
    reviews.extend(soup.find_all('p', class_='partial_entry'))
In [3]:
def make_wordcloud(reviews):
    '''
    makes wordcloud based in review texts
    input: list of reviews from beautifulsoup parsing    
    '''
    reviews = list(map(lambda x: x.contents[0], reviews))
    text = ' '.join(reviews)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(max_font_size=40).generate(text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off');
In [4]:
make_wordcloud(reviews)

There are definite red flags for Haleakala National park.

  • Someone with toddler would have a hard time making it to sunrise or sunset given toddler's sleep time.
  • There are four different mention of car ride (drive, drove, driving, road), which may be difficult for small children.
  • Mention of weather (cold, weather, overcast, wind) does not bode well for children's comorts.

All in all, Haleakala National Park does not seem like a great destination for families with toddlers, which I confirmed by reading through reviews in more depth.

make_wordcloud(reviews2)

In contrast to Haleakala National Park, Baby Beach seems like a great place for toddlers.

  • proper age indications: little, little ones, kid, young, small (although little or small may have to do with the location rather than age)
  • safety: calm, protected, shallow water, shade

Wave may be a red flag, but it is most likely pointing to lack of waves as it is protected. A better natural language processing will filter such results.

Conclusion¶

The prelinary analysis shows that Haleakala National Park, which is recommended as "kid-friendly," is not appropriate for toddlers, while Baby Beach, which does not show up as highly ranked "kid-friendly" destination, is great for toddlers. Therefore, the current recommendation system could be improved upon to identify more suitable destinations for toddlers.
